The paper proposes a novel two-phase neural network model for identifying untrustworthy Web services based on QoS metrics. This involves using a feedforward neural network model and a probabilistic neural network model. The approach is based on machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also deals with security and privacy concerns related to untrustworthy Web services, which are relevant to the cs.CR sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves data collection and analysis, which are associated with the cs.SI and cs.DC sub-categories.
